definition: to have children/to raise or bring up/to educate

sentences.english: Gold was found in the nearby Yukon area of Canada in the eighteen nineties.
sentences.chinese: 十八世纪九十年代在加拿大育空地区附近发现黄金。

sentences.english: Mount Logan is the highest peak in Canada and is located in the Yukon Territory of northwest Canada.
sentences.chinese: 加拿大最高峰，位于加拿大西北部的育空地区。

sentences.english: Discover the complex strategy of Free Cell, Yukon , Deck, and many more.
sentences.chinese: 了解复杂的战略自由细胞，育空，甲板，更多的人。

sentences.english: They crossed the Yukon River and found the bonanza gold.
sentences.chinese: 他们穿越了育空河，找到了黄金富矿。

sentences.english: Fossil found in Yukon are of unknown species.
sentences.chinese: 在育空地区发现的化石属于未知的生物。

sentences.english: Back when I was a young man, my father ran a team of sled dogs up in the YuKon.
sentences.chinese: 当我还小的时候，我父亲在育空山上训练一队雪橇犬。

sentences.english: Thousands of gold seekers traveled to the Yukon through Alaska hoping to get rich.
sentences.chinese: 几千的希望暴富的淘金者穿过阿拉斯加到育空地区。

sentences.english: I went looking for the Yukon Honda motorcycle shop, but it eluded me.
sentences.chinese: 我去寻找育空本田摩托车店，但它未能箱。

sentences.english: Evening settles in over Emerald Lake in Yoho National Park.
sentences.chinese: 夜幕降临在育空国家公园的翡翠湖上。
